11:06.000 --> 11:08.000
Ferdinand is reading the book.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
And where is Gonzalo?

11:10.000 --> 11:13.000
Gonzalo is an old man.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.000
He is sleeping.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
Listen, Your Majesty.

11:18.000 --> 11:20.000
What's that noise?

11:20.000 --> 11:23.000
It's the storm, Antonio.

12:18.000 --> 12:20.000
What's that noise?

12:49.000 --> 12:51.000
Famous shipwrecks.

12:51.000 --> 12:54.000
The Merry Celeste.

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
It is 1872.

12:56.000 --> 12:58.000
A beautiful ship leaves New York.

12:58.000 --> 13:01.000
It is going to Genoa in Italy.

13:01.000 --> 13:05.000
The ship is carrying a lot of barrels of alcohol.

13:05.000 --> 13:10.000
A few months later, the captain of a Portuguese ship, the Gratia,

13:10.000 --> 13:15.000
sees a very strange thing between the islands of the Azores and Portugal.

13:15.000 --> 13:20.000
There is a ship in the sea, but there is no one on it.

13:20.000 --> 13:23.000
Where are the captain and his men?

13:23.000 --> 13:26.000
People call it a ghost ship.

13:26.000 --> 13:31.000
The Portuguese take the ship to Gibraltar, and they use it again,

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
but it brings bad luck.

13:33.000 --> 13:38.000
There is bad weather near Haiti, and the ship sinks there.

13:38.000 --> 13:42.000
Today, many people go to visit the ship.

13:42.000 --> 13:47.000
They dive underwater and try to discover the mystery.

13:47.000 --> 13:52.000
But nobody really knows the true story of the Merry Celeste.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.000
What do you think it is?

13:55.000 --> 13:58.000
The Titanic.

13:58.000 --> 14:05.000
When we think about famous shipwrecks in history, we nearly always think about the Titanic.

14:05.000 --> 14:09.000
Wednesday, the 10th of April 1912.

14:09.000 --> 14:13.000
The Titanic leaves Southampton to sail to New York.

14:13.000 --> 14:17.000
They say it is impossible for the ship to sink.

14:17.000 --> 14:21.000
There are rich people travelling first class.

14:21.000 --> 14:25.000
They want to go to New York because they like travelling.

14:25.000 --> 14:28.000
There are also a lot of poor people.

14:28.000 --> 14:31.000
They travel third class.

14:31.000 --> 14:36.000
They want to start a new life in America.

14:36.000 --> 14:41.000
A few days later, not far from Halifax on the northeast coast of Canada,

14:41.000 --> 14:45.000
the captain sees a big iceberg.

14:45.000 --> 14:50.000
But it is too late, and the ship hits the iceberg.

14:50.000 --> 14:56.000
Eventually, the ship breaks and sinks vertically into the cold sea.

14:56.000 --> 15:01.000
Many people die, but some people escape on lifeboats.

15:01.000 --> 15:06.000
Most of the survivors are first class passengers.

15:06.000 --> 15:11.000
Why do you think this is?

15:17.000 --> 15:22.000
Part 3. More of Ariel's Magic.

15:23.000 --> 15:27.000
All the people from the Kings boat are still alive.

15:27.000 --> 15:31.000
They don't know they are on the island or why they are there.

15:31.000 --> 15:36.000
They are all very tired and they are sleeping.

15:36.000 --> 15:42.000
Ariel calls to Ferdinand and wakes him up by singing sweetly in his ear.

15:42.000 --> 15:48.000
Ferdinand follows the sound of this magical song and meets Prospero and Miranda.

15:49.000 --> 15:51.000
Prospero knows what to do.

15:51.000 --> 15:56.000
He wants Ferdinand and Miranda to fall in love.

15:56.000 --> 16:02.000
Ferdinand immediately thinks Miranda is beautiful and tells her that he loves her.

16:02.000 --> 16:09.000
She tells him that she loves him too, but is it real, or is it only a spell?

16:12.000 --> 16:15.000
Part 3.

16:16.000 --> 16:18.000
Everybody is sleeping.

16:18.000 --> 16:22.000
I must find Ferdinand and wake him.

16:22.000 --> 16:26.000
Time to wake up, time to wake up.

16:26.000 --> 16:30.000
Ferdinand, come with me.

16:30.000 --> 16:34.000
Time to do some magic, time to do some magic.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
Where am I?

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
What's that noise?

16:38.000 --> 16:41.000
I hear a song.

16:41.000 --> 16:44.000
A beautiful song.

16:45.000 --> 16:48.000
It is a beautiful song.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.000
Wait for me.

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
Wait for me.

16:56.000 --> 16:58.000
Here is Ferdinand, sir.

16:58.000 --> 17:01.000
Very good Ariel. You can go now.

17:06.000 --> 17:08.000
Who are you?

17:08.000 --> 17:11.000
What's your name?

17:11.000 --> 17:13.000
My name is Miranda.

17:13.000 --> 17:17.000
You're very beautiful, Miranda.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.000
I love you.

17:19.000 --> 17:21.000
I love you too.

17:26.000 --> 17:30.000
Part 4. An evil plan.

17:30.000 --> 17:34.000
Sebastian and Antonio wake up on the island.

17:34.000 --> 17:41.000
Antonio tells Sebastian to kill his brother, then Sebastian will be King of Naples.

17:41.000 --> 17:48.000
Sebastian agrees to the plan, but he is thinking about Gonzalo, the king's friend.

17:48.000 --> 17:54.000
They must kill him too, or he will know about the king's murder.

17:54.000 --> 17:59.000
But Ariel hears their plan and sings in Gonzalo's ear.

17:59.000 --> 18:06.000
Gonzalo and the king wake up and see Antonio and Sebastian with their swords in the air.

18:06.000 --> 18:11.000
Antonio and Sebastian look very stupid and embarrassed.

18:11.000 --> 18:17.000
They tell a story about wanting to protect the king from some animals.

18:17.000 --> 18:22.000
Fortunately for them, and for Ariel, the king believes their story.

18:22.000 --> 18:27.000
They all go to look for Ferdinand, the king's son.

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
Part 4.

18:34.000 --> 18:38.000
Where are we? Wake up, Sebastian!

18:38.000 --> 18:41.000
We are on an island.

18:41.000 --> 18:47.000
Look, the others are sleeping. This is an excellent opportunity for you, Sebastian.

18:47.000 --> 18:49.000
Why?

18:49.000 --> 18:54.000
If you kill your brother, the king, you can be the new king of Naples.

18:54.000 --> 18:56.000
Good idea.

18:56.000 --> 18:59.000
No. Wait a minute.

19:00.000 --> 19:04.000
Gonzalo is the king's friend.

19:04.000 --> 19:08.000
You kill the king, and I kill Gonzalo.

19:08.000 --> 19:13.000
Okay! Let's do it now, before they wake up.

19:13.000 --> 19:15.000
Are you ready?

19:22.000 --> 19:25.000
Oh no! This is terrible!

19:25.000 --> 19:29.000
I must stop this terrible plan.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
One, two, three.

19:31.000 --> 19:33.000
Time to wake up.

19:33.000 --> 19:37.000
Where are we? Wake up, your Majesty!

19:37.000 --> 19:42.000
What are you doing with your sword, Antonio?

19:42.000 --> 19:45.000
Nothing, your Majesty.

19:45.000 --> 19:48.000
There are lots of dangerous animals on the island.

19:48.000 --> 19:50.000
Yes, we want to protect you.

19:50.000 --> 19:53.000
Very good. Very good.

19:53.000 --> 19:57.000
Now let's find my son, Ferdinand.

20:04.000 --> 20:09.000
Part 5. Caliban's cloak.

20:09.000 --> 20:12.000
Caliban is very sad.

20:12.000 --> 20:18.000
He doesn't want to be Prospero's slave. He complains about his life all the time.

20:18.000 --> 20:24.000
He thinks he hears a bad spirit, so he hides under his cloak.

20:24.000 --> 20:28.000
But the noise is coming from Trinkler, the king's jester.

20:28.000 --> 20:31.000
He is looking for the others.

20:31.000 --> 20:35.000
He hears a storm, and he sees Caliban's cloak.

20:35.000 --> 20:39.000
He decides the cloak is a good place to hide.

20:39.000 --> 20:43.000
The king's butler, Stefano, is walking in the same direction,

20:43.000 --> 20:49.000
and suddenly he too sees a strange shape with lots of legs but no head.

20:49.000 --> 20:52.000
He thinks it is a monster.

20:52.000 --> 20:57.000
Trinkler lifts up the cloak, and is surprised to see Stefano.

20:57.000 --> 21:00.000
Caliban introduces himself.

21:00.000 --> 21:04.000
He tells the jester and the butler all his problems.

21:04.000 --> 21:08.000
He wants to kill Prospero, then he can be free.

21:08.000 --> 21:12.000
Stefano agrees to help Caliban.

21:12.000 --> 21:17.000
Ariel quickly goes to tell Prospero about their plan.

21:19.000 --> 21:22.000
Part 5.

21:22.000 --> 21:26.000
Oh, poor me.

21:26.000 --> 21:30.000
Poor Caliban.

21:30.000 --> 21:35.000
Every day I must work for Prospero.

21:35.000 --> 21:41.000
I want to be free, but I am his slave.

21:41.000 --> 21:46.000
Where are the others? Where's the king? And where's Stefano?

21:46.000 --> 21:50.000
Oh, no. I hear a voice.

21:50.000 --> 21:56.000
It is probably a bad spirit from Prospero.

21:56.000 --> 22:01.000
I must hide.

22:01.000 --> 22:05.000
What a beautiful island. And what is this?

22:05.000 --> 22:09.000
It has arms and legs, but no head.

22:09.000 --> 22:14.000
It is a monster.

22:14.000 --> 22:19.000
Oh, no. Another storm. I must hide.

22:28.000 --> 22:31.000
Where are the others?

22:31.000 --> 22:36.000
Where is the king? And where is Trinkler?

22:36.000 --> 22:39.000
And what is this?

22:39.000 --> 22:49.000
It has forearms and forelegs, but no head.

22:49.000 --> 22:52.000
It is a monster.

22:52.000 --> 22:56.000
Hello, monster. Hello.

22:56.000 --> 23:04.000
Help. Prospero's bad spirits want to torment me.

23:04.000 --> 23:10.000
Oh.

23:10.000 --> 23:14.000
Stefano. Hello. It's me, Trinkler.

23:14.000 --> 23:16.000
And who is he?

23:16.000 --> 23:20.000
I am poor Caliban.

23:20.000 --> 23:26.000
I am Prospero's slave, but I want to be free.

23:26.000 --> 23:29.000
I want to kill Prospero.

23:29.000 --> 23:33.000
That's terrible. You must do something.

23:34.000 --> 23:36.000
We could help you.

23:36.000 --> 23:40.000
No, Stefano. It's not a good idea.

23:40.000 --> 23:46.000
Yes. We must kill Prospero and take control of the island.

23:46.000 --> 23:50.000
Thank you. Thank you.

23:50.000 --> 23:55.000
I must tell Prospero this terrible plan.

23:56.000 --> 24:05.000
Magic and Magicians

24:05.000 --> 24:10.000
Magic is part of the history of many different cultures.

24:10.000 --> 24:15.000
Shakespeare's plays have examples of both good and bad witches.

24:15.000 --> 24:21.000
There are also witches, wizards and magicians in a lot of books and films.

24:22.000 --> 24:26.000
The word magic comes from the word magos.

24:26.000 --> 24:31.000
This is an old word for a priest with special powers.

24:31.000 --> 24:35.000
There are many different opinions about magic.

24:35.000 --> 24:40.000
Some people believe it is possible to explain everything by using science.

24:40.000 --> 24:44.000
Other people think there are special types of energy.

24:44.000 --> 24:52.000
They believe people like wizards and magicians can control this energy and make it do different things.

24:52.000 --> 24:58.000
Today, we often think of magic as a way of doing special tricks or illusions.

24:58.000 --> 25:01.000
The audience does not know the magician's secret.

25:01.000 --> 25:07.000
We are curious to know how he can do such an impossible thing.

25:07.000 --> 25:11.000
The audience must not know about the secrets behind a magic trick.

25:12.000 --> 25:19.000
The enjoyment of magic comes from trying to guess how the magician does his trick.

25:19.000 --> 25:24.000
The magic circle is a special secret society for magicians.

25:24.000 --> 25:31.000
It is only for professional magicians and today there are about 1,500 members.

25:31.000 --> 25:39.000
They must promise not to tell any of the secrets they learn in the magic circle.

25:39.000 --> 25:44.000
A famous escape artist and the master of illusion.

25:44.000 --> 25:48.000
Think back to the late 19th century.

25:48.000 --> 25:52.000
You are in the audience of a famous escape artist.

25:52.000 --> 25:56.000
Harry Houdini is a Hungarian magician.

25:56.000 --> 25:59.000
This is his first big tour.

25:59.000 --> 26:03.000
On stage he is fighting with chains and ropes.

26:03.000 --> 26:05.000
You watch.

26:05.000 --> 26:08.000
Your mouth is open when he frees himself.

26:09.000 --> 26:12.000
Then they put him in a tank full of water.

26:12.000 --> 26:17.000
He is upside down and he has a jacket with many belts.

26:17.000 --> 26:21.000
You think it is impossible for him to escape, but he does.

26:21.000 --> 26:28.000
After he leaves the show, Houdini continues to do his amazing escapes all over the world.

26:28.000 --> 26:32.000
He becomes very famous.

26:32.000 --> 26:35.000
Let's return to the present day.

26:35.000 --> 26:39.000
You are now watching David Copperfield, the master of illusion.

26:39.000 --> 26:42.000
This time he is not in a theatre.

26:42.000 --> 26:44.000
He is on television.

26:44.000 --> 26:48.000
He says he can walk through the great wall of China.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.000
You don't believe anyone can do that.

26:50.000 --> 26:54.000
You think it must be a camera trick, but the people standing next to him

26:54.000 --> 27:00.000
watch his body walk in the wall and go out of the wall on the other side.

27:00.000 --> 27:03.000
Nobody understands how he does it.

27:03.000 --> 27:09.000
He lies in the air over the Grand Canyon like he is lying on a bed of air

27:09.000 --> 27:11.000
and he doesn't fall.

27:11.000 --> 27:16.000
He makes the statue of Liberty disappear and hundreds of people in New York

27:16.000 --> 27:19.000
can't see the statue anymore.

27:19.000 --> 27:25.000
A lot of people are interested in magic, but we don't all believe in it.

27:25.000 --> 27:30.000
What do you think about Houdini and David Copperfield's tricks?

27:30.000 --> 27:34.000
Are they really magic?

27:38.000 --> 27:42.000
Part 6, Delicious Food

27:42.000 --> 27:46.000
Prospero is now ready for the next part of his plan.

27:46.000 --> 27:51.000
It is time for his brother to understand his actions.

27:51.000 --> 27:55.000
Gonzalo is tired and wants to stop and rest.

27:55.000 --> 27:59.000
Antonio thinks this is a good moment to kill Alonzo

27:59.000 --> 28:01.000
and also Gonzalo.

28:01.000 --> 28:05.000
Sebastian tells him to wait until nighttime.

28:05.000 --> 28:09.000
Just at that moment a strange thing happens.

28:09.000 --> 28:15.000
They start to hear some beautiful music and suddenly lots of delicious food arrives.

28:15.000 --> 28:20.000
The king and his men are hungry and they are very surprised and excited.

28:20.000 --> 28:27.000
They imagine themselves eating all this lovely food, but then it suddenly disappears again.

28:27.000 --> 28:31.000
Instead of the food, they see Ariel.

28:31.000 --> 28:35.000
Ariel talks to them about Prospero and Miranda.

28:35.000 --> 28:39.000
She says everything is Antonio's fault.

28:39.000 --> 28:45.000
Antonio remembers his brother Prospero and the evil things of the past.

28:45.000 --> 28:50.000
He knows he is not a good brother, but is he really sorry?

28:50.000 --> 28:55.000
There is the sound of music and Ariel disappears.

28:58.000 --> 29:02.000
Part 6

29:02.000 --> 29:09.000
Ariel, it is time to do some magic. Go to my brother and his friends.

29:09.000 --> 29:13.000
Yes sir, of course sir.

29:17.000 --> 29:21.000
Oh, I am very old.

29:21.000 --> 29:24.000
I am very tired.

29:24.000 --> 29:27.000
Can we stop now?

29:31.000 --> 29:35.000
Kill him now Sebastian. He is very tired.

29:35.000 --> 29:37.000
No, not now.

29:37.000 --> 29:40.000
Tonight when he sleeps.

29:40.000 --> 29:54.000
Look at all this food. I am very hungry.

29:54.000 --> 29:56.000
Let's eat.

29:56.000 --> 29:59.000
Yes, let's eat.

30:05.000 --> 30:09.000
Stop! You are all bad men.

30:10.000 --> 30:18.000
Prospero and Miranda live on this island for 12 years, and it's your fault.

30:18.000 --> 30:26.000
Oh yes, it's true. I am a terrible man, and now I'm very sorry.

30:26.000 --> 30:30.000
My poor brother, poor Miranda.

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
Very good Ariel.

30:34.000 --> 30:37.000
Thank you sir.

30:41.000 --> 30:45.000
It's time to eat, but we have no food.

30:45.000 --> 30:48.000
What can we do? I'm very hungry.

30:48.000 --> 30:50.000
I don't know.

30:50.000 --> 30:52.000
What do you want to eat?

30:52.000 --> 30:55.000
Alonso, what's your favorite food?

30:55.000 --> 31:01.000
Well, I like pasta and pizza. What about you, Gonzalo?

31:01.000 --> 31:06.000
Oh, I'm an old man. I have problems with my teeth.

31:06.000 --> 31:10.000
I only eat soup and ice cream.

31:10.000 --> 31:13.000
Soup and ice cream together?

31:13.000 --> 31:18.000
No, first the soup and then the ice cream.

31:18.000 --> 31:23.000
I like ice cream too, especially chocolate ice cream.

31:23.000 --> 31:26.000
But I don't like soup.

31:26.000 --> 31:30.000
Yes, but Sebastian, what's your favorite food?

31:30.000 --> 31:33.000
I love English food.

31:33.000 --> 31:36.000
Fish and chips is my favorite.

31:36.000 --> 31:42.000
English food is very bad, Sebastian, but we are on an island.

31:42.000 --> 31:44.000
Why don't we eat fish?

31:44.000 --> 31:46.000
Good idea.

31:46.000 --> 31:53.000
If we find some potatoes, we can have fish and chips for dinner.

31:53.000 --> 31:58.000
Now listen to the conversation again.

31:58.000 --> 32:07.000
For questions one to six, tick A, B, or C.

32:07.000 --> 32:11.000
You will listen to the conversation twice.

32:11.000 --> 32:15.000
It's time to eat, but we have no food.

32:15.000 --> 32:19.000
What can we do? I'm very hungry.

32:19.000 --> 32:21.000
I don't know.

32:21.000 --> 32:23.000
What do you want to eat?

32:23.000 --> 32:25.000
Alonso, what's your favorite food?

32:25.000 --> 32:29.000
Well, I like pasta and pizza.

32:29.000 --> 32:31.000
What about you, Gonzalo?

32:31.000 --> 32:34.000
Oh, I'm an old man.

32:34.000 --> 32:37.000
I have problems with my teeth.

32:37.000 --> 32:40.000
I only eat soup and ice cream.

32:40.000 --> 32:44.000
Soup and ice cream together?

32:44.000 --> 32:49.000
No, first the soup and then the ice cream.

32:49.000 --> 32:54.000
I like ice cream too, especially chocolate ice cream.

32:54.000 --> 32:57.000
But I don't like soup.

32:57.000 --> 33:01.000
Yes, but Sebastian, what's your favorite food?

33:01.000 --> 33:04.000
I love English food.

33:04.000 --> 33:07.000
Fish and chips is my favorite.

33:07.000 --> 33:13.000
English food is very bad, Sebastian, but we are on an island.

33:13.000 --> 33:15.000
Why don't we eat fish?

33:15.000 --> 33:17.000
Good idea.

33:17.000 --> 33:22.000
If we find some potatoes, we can have fish and chips for dinner.

33:25.000 --> 33:32.000
Part seven, the bright, beautiful cloak.

33:32.000 --> 33:37.000
Ferdinand and Miranda tell Prospero that they love each other.

33:37.000 --> 33:40.000
Prospero says they can marry.

33:40.000 --> 33:45.000
He makes them beautiful music, and the couple starts dancing.

33:45.000 --> 33:51.000
Prospero is enjoying the music, but he knows something else is happening.

33:51.000 --> 33:56.000
Caliban wants to kill him, and his brother is on the island too.

33:56.000 --> 33:59.000
He tells Ariel about his plan.

33:59.000 --> 34:04.000
Ariel finds Stefano and Trinkilo with Caliban.

34:04.000 --> 34:07.000
They are walking in the forest.

34:07.000 --> 34:10.000
There's lots of water and their clothes are wet.

34:10.000 --> 34:15.000
They see a bright colored cloak, but they cannot see Ariel.

34:15.000 --> 34:19.000
They think it is very beautiful and they want to have it.

34:19.000 --> 34:25.000
They follow the cloak until they see some very big, very angry dogs.

34:25.000 --> 34:28.000
They don't know they are really magic dogs.

34:28.000 --> 34:30.000
They are all very afraid.

34:30.000 --> 34:33.000
They start screaming and they run away.

34:38.000 --> 34:40.000
Part seven.

34:41.000 --> 34:45.000
Now it's time to organize the wedding.

34:45.000 --> 34:47.000
Thank you, father.

34:47.000 --> 34:50.000
I love Ferdinand very much.

34:50.000 --> 34:53.000
And I love Miranda very much.

35:10.000 --> 35:13.000
Stop dancing, I must think.

35:14.000 --> 35:18.000
Stefano, Trinkilo, and Caliban want to kill me.

35:18.000 --> 35:21.000
And my brother is also here on the island.

35:21.000 --> 35:22.000
I have a plan.

35:22.000 --> 35:23.000
Ariel?

35:23.000 --> 35:24.000
Yes, sir.

35:24.000 --> 35:25.000
Yes, sir.

35:25.000 --> 35:26.000
Yes, sir.

35:32.000 --> 35:34.000
Time to do some magic.

35:34.000 --> 35:35.000
Time to do some magic.

35:35.000 --> 35:37.000
One, two, three.

35:37.000 --> 35:38.000
Come with me.

35:38.000 --> 35:40.000
Look at that.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.000
What is it?

35:42.000 --> 35:44.000
It is beautiful.

35:44.000 --> 35:46.000
I want it.

35:46.000 --> 35:47.000
Me too.

35:47.000 --> 35:48.000
Let's go.

35:49.000 --> 35:53.000
Now I will make some magic dogs to scare them.

35:53.000 --> 35:55.000
Go, dogs, go.

36:08.000 --> 36:09.000
Part eight.

36:09.000 --> 36:12.000
Saying sorry.

36:12.000 --> 36:18.000
Ariel takes Alonso, Gonzalo, Sebastian, and Antonio to Prospero.

36:18.000 --> 36:21.000
They say sorry to Prospero.

36:21.000 --> 36:26.000
Prospero is angry, but he decides to forgive them.

36:26.000 --> 36:34.000
Alonso thanks Prospero, but he is still very sad because he thinks his son Ferdinand is dead.

36:34.000 --> 36:37.000
Prospero then gives him the good news.

36:37.000 --> 36:39.000
His son is not dead.

36:39.000 --> 36:41.000
He is with Miranda.

36:41.000 --> 36:45.000
Ferdinand introduces Miranda to his father.

36:45.000 --> 36:51.000
Alonso is pleased about the news about his son and his new daughter.

36:51.000 --> 36:55.000
Just at that moment, Stefano, Trinkilo, and Caliban arrive.

36:55.000 --> 36:57.000
The dogs are behind them.

36:57.000 --> 36:59.000
They are chasing them.

36:59.000 --> 37:05.000
Prospero forgives them as well and tells Caliban he is free.

37:05.000 --> 37:08.000
He can now be master of the island.

37:08.000 --> 37:11.000
He also frees Ariel.

37:11.000 --> 37:14.000
They are both very happy.

37:14.000 --> 37:19.000
Ferdinand and Miranda want to marry as soon as possible.

37:19.000 --> 37:23.000
Prospero does not need to do any more magic now.

37:23.000 --> 37:26.000
He prepares to return to Milan.

37:26.000 --> 37:32.000
But first, he is going to organize a big party for them all.

37:36.000 --> 37:38.000
Part 8

37:40.000 --> 37:44.000
Now, I must speak to my brother Antonio and the others.

37:44.000 --> 37:46.000
Here they are.

37:46.000 --> 37:49.000
I don't believe it, my brother Prospero.

37:49.000 --> 37:53.000
Antonio, you are a bad man.

37:53.000 --> 37:57.000
Sebastian, Alonso, you are bad men too.

37:57.000 --> 38:00.000
Yes, Prospero, you're right.

38:00.000 --> 38:04.000
We are bad men, but we're very sorry now.

38:04.000 --> 38:07.000
My poor brother, I'm very sorry.

38:07.000 --> 38:09.000
Please forgive me.

38:09.000 --> 38:11.000
Of course I forgive you.

38:11.000 --> 38:13.000
I forgive you all.

38:13.000 --> 38:16.000
I am very happy for this.

38:16.000 --> 38:20.000
But I am very sad because my son is lost.

38:20.000 --> 38:22.000
Perhaps he's dead.

38:22.000 --> 38:24.000
No, here is your son.

38:24.000 --> 38:26.000
He's not lost.

38:26.000 --> 38:29.000
He's here with my daughter Miranda.

38:29.000 --> 38:31.000
Father Ferdinand.

38:32.000 --> 38:34.000
This is Miranda.

38:34.000 --> 38:37.000
I love her very much.

38:37.000 --> 38:39.000
We want to get married.

38:39.000 --> 38:41.000
I'm very happy.

38:41.000 --> 38:43.000
This is very good news.

38:43.000 --> 38:45.000
Let's celebrate.

38:46.000 --> 38:53.000
Hello!

38:53.000 --> 38:57.000
Hello!

38:57.000 --> 39:04.000
Oh, Caliban, Stefano, and Trinculo, I forgive you three too.

39:04.000 --> 39:07.000
Thank you, sir.

39:07.000 --> 39:11.000
When I return to Milan with my brother, you can have your island.

39:11.000 --> 39:13.000
You can be master.

39:13.000 --> 39:19.000
Master of the island. Thank you, sir.

39:19.000 --> 39:24.000
And me? Can I live on the island, too?

39:24.000 --> 39:33.000
Yes, Ariel. You and Caliban are now free. You are not my slaves. You can do what you want to do.

39:33.000 --> 39:44.000
Now everything is organized. Tonight, a party, and tomorrow we must return to Milan together.

39:44.000 --> 39:53.000
Ferdinand de Miranda want to get to get married, and Caliban and Ariel can be masters of their island.

39:53.000 --> 40:03.000
I must do no more magic, because our story is finished. If you like it, please clap to break the spell.

